    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-06-05T07:29:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-06-05T07:29:00-05:00" n="540"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d540">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 701.6111/221</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Russia</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_FDR1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Francis</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Petrograd</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-06-05T17:00:00+04:31">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 5, 1918, 5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received June 7, 3.16 a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1. Following just received via Vologda, addressed American Ambassador: <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <p>Russian government nominates as plenipotentiary representative in
                            Washington Citizen <persName>Litvinov</persName> now same in Paris
                            [London]. Hopes friendship your Government will not object our purpose
                            closer relations, intimate friendship between our peoples. Commissary
                            Foreign Affairs, <persName corresp="#p_CGV1">Chicherin</persName>.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>See my telegram of June 5, 6 p.m.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_FDR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Francis</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
